25|$|Barr took a lead in {{legislative}} debate concerning same-sex marriage. He authored and sponsored <b>the</b> <b>Defense</b> <b>of</b> <b>Marriage</b> Act, a law {{enacted in}} 1996 {{which states that}} only marriages that are {{between a man and}} a woman can be federally recognized, and individual states may choose not to recognize a same-sex marriage performed in another state. At the 2008 Libertarian National Convention, he apologized for the part of <b>the</b> <b>Defense</b> <b>of</b> <b>Marriage</b> Act which prevents the federal government from recognizing same-sex marriages.|$|E
